questions.question: What are Binary trees?
questions.Answer: A Binary Tree is a type of data structure that has two nodes: A left node and a right node. In programming, binary trees are actually an extension of the linked list structures.

questions.question: What is a Stack?
questions.Answer: A stack is a data structure in which only the top element can be accessed.

questions.question: What is the difference between NULL and VOID?
questions.Answer: Null is actually a value, whereas Void is a data type identifier.
